summary:
We at least watched Jay-Z's video for "Family Feud". I was surprised to see Brie Larson in it. 
Sure, she'd won her Oscar but...
body:
We at least watched Jay-Z’s video for “Family Feud”. I was surprised to see Brie Larson in it.

Sure, she’d won her Oscar but she wasn’t quite as popular as she is now so I don’t think, in the sea of celebrity cameos, that she was one people were freaking out about a lot at that time.

Still, you know a lot of thought went into the women chosen to have a seat at the table in that scene so it really speaks to Brie’s values and the respect she’s garnered among other women in the industry, even before fans took notice, to be chosen.

Looking beyond fandom to form your own opinion on celebrities and public figures can sometimes be quite rewarding. She’s one of my favorite people.
